abstract.p: Defense Department releases names of 11 more American service members killed in Iraq

block.p: The Department of Defense has identified 3,280 American service members who have died since the start of the Iraq war. It confirmed the deaths of the following Americans this week:
BROWN, Harrison, 31, Staff Sgt., Army; Prichard, Ala.; Third Infantry Division.
EMOLO, Ebe F., 33, Specialist, Army; Greensboro, N.C.; 82nd Airborne Division.
GRASSBAUGH, Jonathan D., 25, Capt., Army; East Hampstead, N.H.; 82nd Airborne Division.
HOOVER, Levi K., 23, Specialist, Army; Midland, Mich.; 82nd Airborne Division.
KENNEDY, Adam P., 25, Sgt., Army; Norfolk, Mass.; 25th Infantry Division.
McCANDLESS, Rodney L., 21, Pfc., Army; Camden, Ark.; 82nd Airborne Division.
MURPHY-SWEET, Philip A., 42, Cmdr., Navy; Caldwell, Idaho; Naval Inventory Control Point, Mechanicsburg, Pa.
SIMMONS, David N., 20, Pfc., Army; Kokomo, Ind.; Third Infantry Division.
SINGLETON, Todd A., 24, Sgt., Army; Muskegon, Mich.; First Cavalry Division.
SPOHN, Clifford A. III, 21, Specialist, Army; Albuquerque; 25th Infantry Division.
WILLIAMS, Jesse L., 25, Staff Sgt., Army; Santa Rosa, Calif.; Second Infantry Division.
